ndupes for Debian
-----------------

This package contains the ndupes duplicate file eliminator, optimized for
memory-constrained environments such as Raspberry Pi and home servers.

Debian-specific notes for this package:

1. Runtime Dependency on SQLite
   ndupes uses a delayed runtime loading mechanism (dlopen) for SQLite.
   While 'ldd' may not show a direct link to libsqlite3, this package
   explicitly depends on 'libsqlite3-0'. If you face any database issues,
   ensure your system's SQLite3 libraries are fully up to date.

2. Filesystem & Hard Link Limitations
   Since ndupes consolidates duplicate files by creating hard links, please
   keep the following in mind:
   - Hard links can only be created within the same filesystem (partition).
     It cannot cross over different mount points.
   - Filesystems like ext4 have an upper limit on the maximum number of
     hard links per file (typically 65,000). While normal use will not
     reach this limit, massive automated link creation might trigger
     filesystem constraints.

